ty3250SysType.name: ty3250SysType
ty3250SysType.description: A textual description of the system model identifier. for example: TYLINK3250

ty3250SysSoftRev.name: ty3250SysSoftRev
ty3250SysSoftRev.description: Displays the Software Revision installed in this node.

ty3250SysHardRev.name: ty3250SysHardRev
ty3250SysHardRev.description: Displays the Hardware Revision of the node.

ty3250SysNumT1Installed.name: ty3250SysNumT1Installed
ty3250SysNumT1Installed.description: The number of network (T1) ports that are installed. There is 1 on the 3250.

ty3250SysNumDteInstalled.name: ty3250SysNumDteInstalled
ty3250SysNumDteInstalled.description: The number of channels (DTE) that are installed. There is 1 on the 3250.

ty3250SysNumCommInstalled.name: ty3250SysNumCommInstalled
ty3250SysNumCommInstalled.description: The number of Maintenance ports that are installed. The front panel MAINT port is for the user interface, the rear panel COMM port is for Lan(Network) Access.

ty3250SysName.name: ty3250SysName
ty3250SysName.description: The user supplied name of the node. This object does not affect operation, but may be useful for network management.

ty3250SysResetNode.name: ty3250SysResetNode
ty3250SysResetNode.description: Command to reset the node. NODE WILL BE OFF-LINE AND USER DATA WILL BE INTERRUPTED FOR APPROXIMATELY 15 SECONDS.

ty3250CfgT1Framing.name: ty3250CfgT1Framing
ty3250CfgT1Framing.description: Type of Framing on this T1 Line. Check with your service provider to determine value. D4 is also known as 'SuperFrame', ESF is 'Extended SuperFrame'. ESF provides enhanced performance monitoring capabilities. ANSI and 54016 refer to the ESF Facility Data Link (FDL).

ty3250CfgT1LineEncoding.name: ty3250CfgT1LineEncoding
ty3250CfgT1LineEncoding.description: T1 interface bipolar encoding scheme. Check with your service provider to determine value. B8ZS, which inherently provides ample 'ones-density', is recommended. AMI users must pay special attention to the 'ones-density' requirements of the servic provider.

ty3250CfgT1Density.name: ty3250CfgT1Density
ty3250CfgT1Density.description: CSU 'ones density' monitor. Defines the maximum number of consecutive zeros that can be transmitted to the network. If density monitoring is enabled, the composite signal is guaranteed to meet the selected density threshhold at the expense of user data. No-density (4) should be used if B8ZS Line Encoding is chosen or if Channel Density is bit-7-stuff. This option is not applicable if DSX-1 mode is selected.

ty3250CfgT1Interface.name: ty3250CfgT1Interface
ty3250CfgT1Interface.description: Enables CSU-specific functions if CSU (1) is selected. CSU functions include Line Build-out, density monitoring, and certain diagnostic features. Selecting DSX-1 (2) will disable these CSU functions for line driver or external CSU applications.

ty3250CfgT1LboSetting.name: ty3250CfgT1LboSetting
ty3250CfgT1LboSetting.description: CSU Line Build Out. Consult service provider for proper setting; either 0dB (1), -7.5dB (2), or -15dB (3). Not applicable if T1Interface = dsx1.

ty3250CfgT1Timing.name: ty3250CfgT1Timing
ty3250CfgT1Timing.description: T1 network interface timing source. There must be only one source on a T1 line. Node should typically be network (2) timed on a point-to-network application. Line Driver and point-to-point applications typically need one node as internal (1), one as network (2).

ty3250CfgT1CicuitID.name: ty3250CfgT1CicuitID
ty3250CfgT1CicuitID.description: This variable contains the transmission vendor's circuit identifier, for the purpose of facilitating troubleshooting.

ty3250CfgDteLineRate.name: ty3250CfgDteLineRate
ty3250CfgDteLineRate.description: Serial Data Rate in bits-per-second, must be multiple of 8000bps. For example enter 768000 for 768Kb/s. Valid rates depend upon channel density selection: nX56K for bit-7-stuffing, and nX64K for clear-channel (n is an integer 1-24 inclusive).

ty3250CfgDteChannelDensity.name: ty3250CfgDteChannelDensity
ty3250CfgDteChannelDensity.description: Packing of serial data into T1 DS0's. Bit-7-stuff (56) allows DTE rates of nX56Kb/s and provides sufficient ones-density on any circuit. Clear-channel (64) allows rates on nX64Kb/s and may require an additional means of density enforcement (eg, B8ZS).

ty3250CfgDteTiming.name: ty3250CfgDteTiming
ty3250CfgDteTiming.description: Serial DTE Transmit Timing mode. Loop-1 (1) uses the clock returned from the DTE (TT/TCE) to sample tx data, Loop-2 (2) uses the clock (ST/TC) generated by the node to sample tx data.

ty3250CfgDteClockMode.name: ty3250CfgDteClockMode
ty3250CfgDteClockMode.description: Clock-normal samples data with the rising edge of the selected tx clock, clock-invert samples data with the falling edge of the selected tx clock. The tx clock is selected using CfgDteTiming. This clock invertion is most useful when loop-2 timing is used. Only in rare circumstances will clock-invert (2) be used with loop-1 timing.

ty3250CfgDteDataMode.name: ty3250CfgDteDataMode
ty3250CfgDteDataMode.description: Inverts data. Can make some applications, particularly HDLC-based protocols, meet density requirements even across clear channel DS0s in AMI mode.

ty3250CfgDteIntfType.name: ty3250CfgDteIntfType
ty3250CfgDteIntfType.description: Sets the electrical interface for the DTE port.

ty3250ConnAutoT1Index.name: ty3250ConnAutoT1Index
ty3250ConnAutoT1Index.description: Index to T1 network port of interest. 3250 supports one T1 network port (1)

ty3250ConnStartDS0.name: ty3250ConnStartDS0
ty3250ConnStartDS0.description: Port1-t1 includes 24 DS0's. This value is the starting DS0 used by the node to allocate DS0s to meet port2-dte's requirements. Sequential, contiguous DS0s are assigned. The number of DS0s required is based upon the DTE Data Rate and DTE Channel Mapping. The node's response to an entry may be gathered by querying ty3250ConnAutoStatus. To assign DS0s in a non-contiguous format, use the CfgEditConnTable.

ty3250ConnAutoPort.name: ty3250ConnAutoPort
ty3250ConnAutoPort.description: Selects the port for which DS0s are automatically allocated to on the T1 network port. Node software may not allow connection of port1-t1 to port1-t1.

ty3250ConnAutoType.name: ty3250ConnAutoType
ty3250ConnAutoType.description: Defines the type of traffic being transported. The 3250 only supports data (1). The selected type will be assigned to all DS0s.

ty3250ConnDteRate.name: ty3250ConnDteRate
ty3250ConnDteRate.description: Data rate of the 3250's DTE port. Can be changed from the CfgDteTable.

ty3250ConnDteDensity.name: ty3250ConnDteDensity
ty3250ConnDteDensity.description: Channel/DS0 format for the 3250's DTE port. Can be changed from the CfgDteTable.

ty3250ConnDs0Required.name: ty3250ConnDs0Required
ty3250ConnDs0Required.description: The number of DS0s required by the node's DTE port. This is based upon the DTE data rate and channel density selections.

ty3250ConnAutoStatus.name: ty3250ConnAutoStatus
ty3250ConnAutoStatus.description: Queries the node's connection status. Cause codes will be returned when a connection set is rejected.

ty3250CfgCurrentConnTable.name: ty3250CfgCurrentConnTable
ty3250CfgCurrentConnTable.description: Retrieves node's active connections assignments for display only. To edit connections, use CfgConnAutoAssign or CfgEditConnTable.

ty3250CfgCurrentConnections.name: ty3250CfgCurrentConnections
ty3250CfgCurrentConnections.description: An entry in the Current Connections Table.

ty3250T1Index.name: ty3250T1Index
ty3250T1Index.description: Index to T1 network port of interest. 3250 only supports one T1 network port (1)

ty3250Ds0.name: ty3250Ds0
ty3250Ds0.description: DS0 number 1 through 24 corresponding to the T1 network port index

ty3250DtePort.name: ty3250DtePort
ty3250DtePort.description: DS0 assignment for indexed T1 network port. After making any adjustments to the connections, the ty3250CfgConnUpdateCmd must be sent. Node software may not permit port1-t1 connections to itself.

ty3250Type.name: ty3250Type
ty3250Type.description: Defines the type of traffic being transported. The 3250 only supports data (1).

ty3250CfgEditConnCopyCurrtoEdit.name: ty3250CfgEditConnCopyCurrtoEdit
ty3250CfgEditConnCopyCurrtoEdit.description: Fill the edit buffer with the node's current active connections.

ty3250CfgEditConnTable.name: ty3250CfgEditConnTable
ty3250CfgEditConnTable.description: Edits current DS0 assignment. After making any adjustments to the connections, the ty3250CfgConnUpdateCmd must be sent.

ty3250CfgEditConnEntry.name: ty3250CfgEditConnEntry
ty3250CfgEditConnEntry.description: An entry in the Edit Connections table.

ty3250ConnT1Index.name: ty3250ConnT1Index
ty3250ConnT1Index.description: Index to T1 network port of interest. 3250 only supports one T1 network port (1)

ty3250ConnDS0.name: ty3250ConnDS0
ty3250ConnDS0.description: DS0 number 1 through 24 corresponding to the T1 network port index

ty3250ConnDTE.name: ty3250ConnDTE
ty3250ConnDTE.description: DS0 assignment for indexed T1 network port. After making any adjustments to the connections, the ty3250CfgConnUpdateCmd must be sent. Node software may not permit connections between port1-t1 and itself.

ty3250ConnType.name: ty3250ConnType
ty3250ConnType.description: defines the type of traffic being transported. The 3250 only supports data (1).

ty3250CfgConnUpdateCmd.name: ty3250CfgConnUpdateCmd
ty3250CfgConnUpdateCmd.description: Updates the connections with the edit buffer. The edit buffer is comprised of any changes sent (set) from the CfgEditConnTable.

ty3250CfgConnStatus.name: ty3250CfgConnStatus
ty3250CfgConnStatus.description: Displays node status from the last connection update.

ty3250CfgEditConnClearEditBuff.name: ty3250CfgEditConnClearEditBuff
ty3250CfgEditConnClearEditBuff.description: Removes all changes from edit buffer. The edit buffer is comprised of any changes sent (set) from the CfgEditConnTable.

ty3250CfgCommIntf.name: ty3250CfgCommIntf
ty3250CfgCommIntf.description: Configuration of electrical interface and character format of the communications ports.

ty3250CfgCommIndex.name: ty3250CfgCommIndex
ty3250CfgCommIndex.description: The comm (1) is at the rear and the maint (2) is at the front of the box.

ty3250CfgCommBaud.name: ty3250CfgCommBaud
ty3250CfgCommBaud.description: Baud rate for this Communication port. Values are baud-1200 (1), baud-2400 (2), baud-4800 (3), baud-9600 (4), baud-19200 (5), baud-38400 (6).

ty3250CfgCommDataBits.name: ty3250CfgCommDataBits
ty3250CfgCommDataBits.description: Databits for this Communication port. Values are databits-7 (1) and databits-8 (2).

ty3250CfgCommStopBits.name: ty3250CfgCommStopBits
ty3250CfgCommStopBits.description: Number of Stopbits for this Communication port. Values are stopbits-1 (1), stopbits-1-5 (2), and stopbits-2 (3).

ty3250CfgCommParity.name: ty3250CfgCommParity
ty3250CfgCommParity.description: Parity for this Communication port. Values are no-parity (1), odd-parity (2), even-parity (3).

ty3250CfgCommFlowCtrl.name: ty3250CfgCommFlowCtrl
ty3250CfgCommFlowCtrl.description: Flow Control for this Communication port. Values are off-flow-control (1) and on-flow-control (2).

ty3250CfgCommModeIndex.name: ty3250CfgCommModeIndex
ty3250CfgCommModeIndex.description: Communication port configured as user interface. The comm (1) is at the rear and the maint (2) is at the front of the box. The 3250 may require that the maint (2) port be used for user interface only.

ty3250CfgCommMode.name: ty3250CfgCommMode
ty3250CfgCommMode.description: Defines mode of operation of the selected communication port. The 3250 may require that the user-interface be assigned to the Maint port and a Network access type be assigned to the COMM port.

ty3250CfgCommMyIP.name: ty3250CfgCommMyIP
ty3250CfgCommMyIP.description: The IP address for this node's network access port.

ty3250CfgCommPeerIP.name: ty3250CfgCommPeerIP
ty3250CfgCommPeerIP.description: The IP address for other end of network access connection.

ty3250CfgCommMask.name: ty3250CfgCommMask
ty3250CfgCommMask.description: The IP Network Mask (eg 255.255.255.0) for the network access link.

ty3250CfgCommMaxMTU.name: ty3250CfgCommMaxMTU
ty3250CfgCommMaxMTU.description: The Maximum Transmission Unit is the size of the largest IP packet supported. This value should be set to the lowest value supported by any equipment in the transmission path.

ty3250CfgSnmpTable.name: ty3250CfgSnmpTable
ty3250CfgSnmpTable.description: IP addresses and corresponding trap filters.

ty3250SnmpEntry.name: ty3250SnmpEntry
ty3250SnmpEntry.description: entry of IP addresses and corresponding trap filters.

ty3250SnmpIndex.name: ty3250SnmpIndex
ty3250SnmpIndex.description: The index to one of the SNMP manager's address and filter configurations.

ty3250SnmpManagerIP.name: ty3250SnmpManagerIP
ty3250SnmpManagerIP.description: The IP address for the SNMP manager to receive this node's TRAPs.

ty3250DiagT1LocLineLpbk.name: ty3250DiagT1LocLineLpbk
ty3250DiagT1LocLineLpbk.description: Local Line Loopback on the T1 network port. Data and framing received from the network is transmitted back to the network

ty3250DiagT1LocPylLpbk.name: ty3250DiagT1LocPylLpbk
ty3250DiagT1LocPylLpbk.description: Local Payload Loopback on the T1 network port. Data (NOT framing) received from the network is reframed and transmitted back to the network.

ty3250DiagT1LocAggrLpbk.name: ty3250DiagT1LocAggrLpbk
ty3250DiagT1LocAggrLpbk.description: Local Aggregate Loopback on the T1 network port. Data from the DTE is framed for transmission and looped back through the network receiver towards the DTE.

ty3250DiagT1RmtLpbkStatus.name: ty3250DiagT1RmtLpbkStatus
ty3250DiagT1RmtLpbkStatus.description: Status of Remote Loopbacks received from the T1 network port. csu-lpbk-from-remote (1) indicates the node is in a Network Line Loopback state due to the reception of the CSU Loop-up pattern from the network. dsu-lpbk-from-remote (2) indicates the node is in a Network Line Loopback state due to the reception of the TyLink proprietary Loop-up pattern a remote node. pyl-lpbk-from-remote (3) indicates the node is in a Payload Loopback state due to the reception of the Facility Data Link's Loop-up pattern from the network (ESF only). csu-lpbk-sent-to-remote (4) indicates the node sent a csu loop up pattern to the remote. The node doesn't know if the loopback was accepted by the remote unit. dsu-lpbk-sent-to-remote (5) indicates the node sent a dsu loop up pattern to the remote. The node doesn't know if the loopback was accepted by the remote unit.

ty3250DiagT1RmtLpbkCmd.name: ty3250DiagT1RmtLpbkCmd
ty3250DiagT1RmtLpbkCmd.description: Remote loopbacks that can be transmitted out the T1 network port. rmt-csu-lpbk-loopup (1) sends standard CSU loop up code into the network. rmt-csu-lpbk-loopdown (2) sends standard CSU loop down code into the network. rmt-dsu-lpbk-loopup (3) sends TyLink proprietary loop up code into the network. rmt-dsu-lpbk-loopdown (4) sends TyLink proprietary loop up code into the network.

ty3250DiagDteLocBidirLpbk.name: ty3250DiagDteLocBidirLpbk
ty3250DiagDteLocBidirLpbk.description: Local Bi-directional Loopback on the DTE port. Loops the clock and data back to the DTE at the interface on the 3250; also loops the DTE's network bandwidth back to the network.

ty3250DiagDteRmtLpbkStatus.name: ty3250DiagDteRmtLpbkStatus
ty3250DiagDteRmtLpbkStatus.description: Status of Remote Loopbacks received for the DTE port. bidir-lpbk-from-remote indictaes that either a proprietary or V54 loop up pattern was received on the DTE's network bandwidth. bidir-lpbk-sent-to-remote indiactes that either a proprietary or V54 loop up pattern was sent to the remote DTE.

ty3250DiagDteRmtLpbkCmd.name: ty3250DiagDteRmtLpbkCmd
ty3250DiagDteRmtLpbkCmd.description: Remote loopbacks that can be transmitted to a remote DTE port rmt-bidir-lpbk-loopup-tyl (1) sends the TyLink proprietary loop up pattern to a remote TyLink DTE. When detected by the remote unit, a DTE Bidirectional Loopback is put up. rmt-bidir-lpbk-loopdown-tyl (2) sends the TyLink proprietary loop down pattern to a remote TyLink DTE. When detected by the remote unit, a DTE Bidirectional Loopback is torn down. rmt-bidir-lpbk-loopup-V54 (3) sends the standard V.54 loop up pattern to a remote, V54-compatible DTE. When detected by the remote unit, a DTE Bidirectional Loopback is put up. rmt-bidir-lpbk-loopdown-V54 (4) sends the standard V.54 loop down pattern to a remote, V54-compatible DTE. When detected by the remote unit, a DTE Bidirectional Loopback is torn down.

ty3250DiagBerPattrn.name: ty3250DiagBerPattrn
ty3250DiagBerPattrn.description: selects pseudorandom pattern for bit error rate test

ty3250DiagBerState.name: ty3250DiagBerState
ty3250DiagBerState.description: BERT test related actions: a: Starts a BERT test on selected bandwidth, b: Stops a BERT test on selected bandwidth, c: Inject Errors while the BERT test is running, d: Clears BERT test errors.

ty3250DiagBerStatus.name: ty3250DiagBerStatus
ty3250DiagBerStatus.description: Displays the current BERT test sync status.

ty3250DiagBerErrors.name: ty3250DiagBerErrors
ty3250DiagBerErrors.description: Displays the number of errors detected in Bert Test.

ty3250DiagBerTimeElaps.name: ty3250DiagBerTimeElaps
ty3250DiagBerTimeElaps.description: Elapsed time since BERT test was started or cleared.

ty3250PortStatusTable.name: ty3250PortStatusTable
ty3250PortStatusTable.description: Status of a T1 or DTE port.

ty3250PortStatus.name: ty3250PortStatus
ty3250PortStatus.description: An entry in the DS1 Interval table.

ty3250IntfIndex.name: ty3250IntfIndex
ty3250IntfIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the interface to which this entry is applicable.

ty3250IntfMode.name: ty3250IntfMode
ty3250IntfMode.description: Status of the indexed port. Inactive (1) indicates the port has no connections. Active (2) indicates connections and data mode. Test-mode (3) indicates connections and diagnostic state for that port.

ty3250IntfAlarms.name: ty3250IntfAlarms
ty3250IntfAlarms.description: Alarms present at the indexed port. The node software may not support DTE alarm conditions.

ty3250PerfT1CurrentTable.name: ty3250PerfT1CurrentTable
ty3250PerfT1CurrentTable.description: The T1 performance numbers for the current 15 minute interval.

ty3250T1CurrentEntry.name: ty3250T1CurrentEntry
ty3250T1CurrentEntry.description: An entry in the T1 Current Perf table.

ty3250T1CurrentIndex.name: ty3250T1CurrentIndex
ty3250T1CurrentIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the T1 interface to which this entry is applica- ble.

ty3250T1CurrentCrc6Events.name: ty3250T1CurrentCrc6Events
ty3250T1CurrentCrc6Events.description: Count of CRC errors detected on an ESF framed circuit. In ESF framing a CRC is generated at the source, based upon the composite data. A CRC error indicates the presence of at least one bit error in an ESF superframe. This field is a free-running accumulation of CRC errors and IS NOT reset when the current 15 minute interval expires. It can be reset with the performance command ty3250T1PerfClearEvents. Not applicable if D4/SF framing is selcted.

ty3250T1CurrentOofEvents.name: ty3250T1CurrentOofEvents
ty3250T1CurrentOofEvents.description: Count of Out-of-Frame events on a T1 circuit. An out-of- frame event occurs when the frame synchronization criteria is lost and a resynchronization must occur. Data is interrupted during frame resynchronization. This field is a free-running accumulation of OOF transitions and IS NOT reset when the current 15 minute interval expires. It can be reset with the performance command ty3250T1PerfClearEvents.

ty3250T1CurrentESs.name: ty3250T1CurrentESs
ty3250T1CurrentESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds, encountered by a T1 interface in the current 15 minute inter- val. An errored second is a one-second interval with CRC errors or a loss of frame sync occurred.

ty3250T1CurrentSESs.name: ty3250T1CurrentSESs
ty3250T1CurrentSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A severely errored second is a one second interval with more than 320 CRC errors or one or more frame sync losses.

ty3250T1CurrentSEFSs.name: ty3250T1CurrentSEFSs
ty3250T1CurrentSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A SEFS is a one second interval with one or more frame sync losses.

ty3250T1CurrentUASs.name: ty3250T1CurrentUASs
ty3250T1CurrentUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute in- terval. A UAS is a one second interval during which the received signal is classified as 'unavailable due to excessive errors'. A signal is unavailable after receiving ten consective severely errored seconds and stays unavailable until ten seconds without a severely errored second occur.

ty3250T1CurrentCSSs.name: ty3250T1CurrentCSSs
ty3250T1CurrentCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A controlled slip is the replication or deletion of a T1 frame at the receiver. These events often indicate a T1 network timing problem.

ty3250T1CurrentBESs.name: ty3250T1CurrentBESs
ty3250T1CurrentBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds (BESs) encountered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. A BES is a one second interval with more than one and less than 320 CRC errors.

ty3250T1CurrentLCVs.name: ty3250T1CurrentLCVs
ty3250T1CurrentLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs) en- countered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. LCVs are non-B8ZS related violations of the alternate mark inversion protocol. An excessive count usually indicates a B8ZS/AMI configuration mismatch in the T1 network.

ty3250T1IntervalEntry.name: ty3250T1IntervalEntry
ty3250T1IntervalEntry.description: An entry in the DS1 Interval table.

ty3250T1IntervalIndex.name: ty3250T1IntervalIndex
ty3250T1IntervalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the t1 interface to which this entry is applica- ble. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value as a NetwLineIndex object instance.

ty3250T1IntervalNumber.name: ty3250T1IntervalNumber
ty3250T1IntervalNumber.description: A number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the least recently completed 15 minutes inter- val (assuming that all 96 intervals are valid).

ty3250T1IntervalESs.name: ty3250T1IntervalESs
ty3250T1IntervalESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, indi- vidual 15 minute, intervals. An errored second is a one-second interval with CRC errors or a loss of frame sync occurred.

ty3250T1IntervalSESs.name: ty3250T1IntervalSESs
ty3250T1IntervalSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A severely errored second is a one second interval with more than 320 CRC errors or one or more frame sync losses.

ty3250T1IntervalSEFSs.name: ty3250T1IntervalSEFSs
ty3250T1IntervalSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A SEFS is a one second interval with one or more frame sync losses.

ty3250T1IntervalUASs.name: ty3250T1IntervalUASs
ty3250T1IntervalUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A UAS is a one second interval during which the received signal is classified as 'unavailable due to excessive errors'. A signal is unavailable after receiving ten consective severely errored seconds and stays unavailable until ten seconds without a severely errored second occur.

ty3250T1IntervalCSSs.name: ty3250T1IntervalCSSs
ty3250T1IntervalCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A controlled slip is the replication or deletion of a T1 frame at the receiver. These events often indicate a T1 network timing problem.

ty3250T1IntervalBESs.name: ty3250T1IntervalBESs
ty3250T1IntervalBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds (BESs) encountered by a t1 interface in one of the previous 96, individual 15 minute, intervals. A BES is a one second interval with more than one and less than 320 CRC errors.

ty3250T1IntervalLCVs.name: ty3250T1IntervalLCVs
ty3250T1IntervalLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs) en- countered by a DS1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. LCVs are non-B8ZS related violations of the alternate mark inversion protocol. An excessive count usually indicates a B8ZS/AMI configuration mismatch in the T1 network.

ty3250PerfT1TotalTable.name: ty3250PerfT1TotalTable
ty3250PerfT1TotalTable.description: The T1 Total table. 24 hour interval.

ty3250T1TotalEntry.name: ty3250T1TotalEntry
ty3250T1TotalEntry.description: An entry in the T1 Total table.

ty3250T1TotalIndex.name: ty3250T1TotalIndex
ty3250T1TotalIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the t1 interface to which this entry is applica- ble. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value as a NetwLineIndex object instance.

ty3250T1TotalESs.name: ty3250T1TotalESs
ty3250T1TotalESs.description: The number of Errored Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. An errored second is a one-second interval with CRC errors or a loss of frame sync occurred.

ty3250T1TotalSESs.name: ty3250T1TotalSESs
ty3250T1TotalSESs.description: The number of Severely Errored Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. A severely errored second is a one second interval with more than 320 CRC errors or one or more frame sync losses.

ty3250T1TotalSEFSs.name: ty3250T1TotalSEFSs
ty3250T1TotalSEFSs.description: The number of Severely Errored Framing Seconds 24 hour interval. A SEFS is a one second interval with one or more frame sync losses.

ty3250T1TotalUASs.name: ty3250T1TotalUASs
ty3250T1TotalUASs.description: The number of Unavailable Seconds encountered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour in- terval. A UAS is a one second interval during which the received signal is classified as 'unavailable due to excessive errors'. A signal is unavailable after receiving ten consective severely errored seconds and stays unavailable until ten seconds without a severely errored second occur.

ty3250T1TotalCSSs.name: ty3250T1TotalCSSs
ty3250T1TotalCSSs.description: The number of Controlled Slip Seconds encoun- tered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. A controlled slip is the replication or deletion of a T1 frame at the receiver. These events often indicate a T1 network timing problem.

ty3250T1TotalBESs.name: ty3250T1TotalBESs
ty3250T1TotalBESs.description: The number of Bursty Errored Seconds (BESs) encountered by a t1 interface in the previous 24 hour interval. A BES is a one second interval with more than one and less than 320 CRC errors.

ty3250T1TotalLCVs.name: ty3250T1TotalLCVs
ty3250T1TotalLCVs.description: The number of Line Code Violations (LCVs) en- countered by a t1 interface in the current 15 minute interval. LCVs are non-B8ZS related violations of the alternate mark inversion protocol. An excessive count usually indicates a B8ZS/AMI configuration mismatch in the T1 network.

ty3250T1PerfCmdTypeTable.name: ty3250T1PerfCmdTypeTable
ty3250T1PerfCmdTypeTable.description: An entry in the DS1 Interval table.

ty3250T1PerfCmdType.name: ty3250T1PerfCmdType
ty3250T1PerfCmdType.description: An entry in the DS1 Interval table.

ty3250T1CommandIndex.name: ty3250T1CommandIndex
ty3250T1CommandIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the t1 interface to which this command is applica- ble.

ty3250T1PerfFreezeState.name: ty3250T1PerfFreezeState
ty3250T1PerfFreezeState.description: This command halts the node's performance monitoring and freezes the current, interval, and total performance register values.

ty3250T1PerfClearEvents.name: ty3250T1PerfClearEvents
ty3250T1PerfClearEvents.description: This command resets all of the (user's) error event registers. This includes the CRC6 and Out-of-Frame counts. It does not affect the interval or 24 hour performance totals.

ty3250T1PerfClearAll.name: ty3250T1PerfClearAll
ty3250T1PerfClearAll.description: This command resets all of the (user's) performance registers.

ty3250AlarmType.name: ty3250AlarmType
ty3250AlarmType.description: The type of alarms that are generated on the node

ty3250Trap.name: ty3250Trap
ty3250Trap.description: A ty3250Trap trap signifies that the sending node had its `ty3250AlarmType` variable modified.
